column2: UPDATE 3-U.S. court halts $8.2 bln Activision deal with Vivendi SAN FRANCISCO/PARIS
column3: Sept 19 A U.S. court has taken the rare step of halting Vivendi SA's $8.2 billion deal to sell most of its stake in Activision Blizzard Inc back to the U.S. videogame publisher
column4: but the move is unlikely to kill the transaction
column5: according to analysts and legal experts.

column2: INSIGHT-Embraer's Herculean task: Brazilian jet takes on Lockheed By Brad Haynes     SAO JOSE DOS CAMPOS
column4: Sept 19 For decades Brazilian planemaker Embraer SA has kept its head down
column5: shying away from larger aircraft in competition with industry giants that its executives called the "big dogs."     A military cargo plane trundling down the runway is about to change that.      In a direct challenge to Lockheed Martin Corp's  storied Hercules airlifter
column6: Embraer is promising a jet that flies higher
column7: fuller and faster - at a lower price.     The
